org.omancode.r.types
Class RVectorList

java.lang.Object
  org.omancode.r.types.RVectorList
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<RVector>, java.util.Collection<RVector>, java.util.List<RVector>
public class RVectorList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.List<RVector>

A list of RVectors. Can be created from POJO collections, an RList or Casper dataset. Provides method to convert to an RList for use with R. Used to represent POJO collections or Casper datasets in R.

Version:
$Revision: 53 $
Author:
Oliver Mannion

RVectorList

public RVectorList(java.util.Collection<?> col,
                   java.lang.Class<?> stopClass)
            throws java.beans.IntrospectionException
Create an list of RVectors from the given Collection. Introspection is used to determine the bean properties (i.e.: getter methods) that are exposed, and each one becomes a vector. Vectors are only created for primitive properties and arrays of primitive properties; object properties are ignored without warning. NB: doesn't automatically create factors for vectors like read.table does.

Parameters:
col - the Java collection to convert.
stopClass - Columns are created for all getter methods that are defined by stopClass's subclasses. stopClass's getter methods and superclass getter methods are not converted to columns in the dataframe.
Throws:
java.beans.IntrospectionException - if problem reading properties of the collection

RVectorList

public RVectorList(java.util.List<java.lang.String> names,
                   java.util.List<java.lang.Class<?>> types,
                   int numElements)
Create a list of empty RVectors from list of names and types. Types that cannot be handled will be silently ignored. Each RVector will be empty and initialised to numElements .

Parameters:
names - list of names of the vectors to create
types - list of types of the vectors to create
numElements - initial size of each vector

Method Detail

addCMarkedUpRow

public RVectorList addCMarkedUpRow(java.util.Collection<? extends CMarkedUpRowBean> col)
                            throws java.beans.IntrospectionException
Add the columns in a CMarkedUpRow as vectors to this RVectorList. The additional columns/vectors are filled by the CMarkedUpRows retrieved from a collection of CMarkedUpRowBeans. If a CMarkedUpRow is not returned by the first CMarkedUpRowBean then this method will silently exit.

Parameters:
col - collection of beans that expose a CMarkedUpRow.
Returns:
this RVectorList. Will now contain the added columns/vectors.
Throws:
java.beans.IntrospectionException - if problem reading collection.
